=== apiFetch refresh-fail path trace ===
When doRefresh() returns null (refresh token not in DB):
 isRefreshing = false
 queue.forEach(reject) is called for queued requests
 queue = []
 newToken is null, so the retry block is skipped
 res still points to the original 401 response object
 Code falls through to: if (!res.ok) - TRUE since 401 is not ok
 err = await res.json() - reads the 401 response body
 throws Error(Missing or malformed Authorization header)

=== apiFetch successful refresh path trace ===
When doRefresh() returns a new token:
 saveTokens(newAt, newRt) was called inside doRefresh
 attachAuth(newToken) sets headers[Authorization] = Bearer newToken
 doRequest() calls attachAuth(getTokens().accessToken) - same newToken from localStorage
 fetch is retried with valid token - succeed
